Rebuke: Problems
To the Editor:
I know lt's a bit early to
make sleeping congratulations
of the kind I am going to make
about Grimell, but as a newcomer whose expectations
about the place have rather
fallen short, I feel completed
to speak.
First, this campus boxes the
hell out of me. Compared to
computer I've been on during
the past three years (Northwestern and Yale), the Intellectual excitement and percent
here is almost nil. The sell job
I got before I came was largely based on how intense, bright,
and scintillating all these still
cents were going to be. Yet I
must say that after nearly six
weeks here i have yet to hear
anyone talk spontaneously about
what he is reading, either in
class or out, let alone talk about
his classes. I have yet to hear
any passionate discussion or
race, politics, religion, art, eco<
comics, transcripts, or comic
strips. In fact I have yet to
hear any passionate discussion
of anything but the opens “issue", which is little more than
narcissism in its worst form
coupled with is children exhibitionism (e.g., destinations of
home rule and publicized constitution), Whatever intensity exists here is certainly not academic, though there may be a
great deal of international intensity. (I will admit that there
is a fair amount of booking going on and I am not at all talking about those people who
haven't emerald from the
stocks for six weeks and have
developed a kind of synthetic
relationship with their barrel.
Obviously, these people cannon
make the campus a more exciting place. vcr a person to
be so designated by what he
reads that he can never fear
himself away from it seems to
me to be a contamination in
terms.)
The only issue-oriented activity on the campus which
reaches to all members of the
community is the Pterodactyl.
Here I will have to admit that
despite all its sexual hanging
and worn-out New Left marriage, the Pierudaiclyl l5 passionate. Despite all its misdirected
historic about Administration.
